17/03/2009
ISTANBUL, Turkey -- World leaders on the sidelines of the Fifth World Water Forum in Istanbul on Monday (March 16th) called for urgent measures regarding management of water resources around the globe. The leaders signed a joint statement appealing for concrete action by all governments to highlight the role water plays in development and society. The leaders underscored the need for new policies, strategic adjustments and institutional reforms regarding water. The statement will go to the G8 countries and the UN as a basis for preparing more comprehensive international documents. Police used tear gas against protestors who tried to march to the forum venue. (Turkiye, Zaman, Yeni Safak, Cumhuriyet, Radikal, Sabah - 17/03/09; Anadolu news agency, Hurriyet, Reuters, Xinhua - 16/03/09)
